Console.WriteLine("Syntax error: ultem.exe [-f <String>] [-s <String>] [-x <String>] [-v on|off] [-o on|off]\nThe available options are:\n-f <file name or full file path>: specifies a file to be loaded (incompatible with -x)\n-s <server name>: name of the server to use (localhost by default)\n-x <command>: specifies a UserLock command to execute\n-v on|off: specifies if the log level should be verbose or not\n-o on|off: specifies if the server ouput flow must be displayed (on) or not (off)\n-u <domain name>\\<user name>: specifies a user to impersonate\n-p <password>: specifies a password of the user to impersonate\n-b on|off: enables or disables timing benchmark\n-l on|off: locate server mode\n-e <nb of bytes>: makes an echo test");